title: butterfly_net
body:
A type of [[hand net]] used for capturing [[butterfly|butterflies]].  For tagging purposes this is used for any type of net used for capturing bugs.

A butterfly net has a fine lightweight mesh netting to prevent damaging the wings of a butterfly.  For capturing bugs from brush and vegetation a sweep net is used. The netting of a sweep net is typically made of sturdier material than a butterfly net, such as sail cloth.

title: imageboard_desourced
body:
From February of 2008 up to Late November of 2016, Danbooru rewrote select imageboard sources to "Image board" on upload, such as those from 4chan, Cynthia and Yande.re. Due to the nature of things, it is unlikely for those automatic changes to be reversed. (forum #122820)

As a result, post with such sources have automatically received the [[non-web source]] tag, due to their now-textual nature.

This tag is for such posts (as well as those posts that were manually desourced from their original by users uploading). If possible, the sources should be standardized for ease of access (forum #152518), if not restored if in any way possible. Posts which have had their sources changed to either their original first-party source, a different text source, or to nothing cannot reasonably be accounted for.

If the source is changed to the image's original first-party source, assuming the source in question is still active, and the md5/EXIF data might not match, please use topic #16765 to get the post replaced. For first-party sources that aren't available anymore ([[bad id]]), check tools such as SauceNAO and ascii2d, as to see if a link to them can still be obtained (though in such a case, this tag could arguably be retained on the post in question, due to how imageboards can potentially change that data; or if not, substituted with [[MD5 mismatch]] where appropriate).

body:
[i]Provence, Catastrophe Messenger of Rhodes Island, always keeps an eye on the movements of Catastrophes and the enemy.[/i]

A playable Sniper Operator in [[Arknights]].

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Siracusa[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]November 30[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Lupo[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]162 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]1 year[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]

Provence is a Catastrophe Messenger, tasked with investigating Catastrophe zones and providing early warnings of impending Catastrophes. Also a staunch environmentalist and an advocate of resource conservation.

Her most notable feature is her big, fluffy tail, which she grooms on her free time.

Uses a compound crossbow during combat. Her callsign is a reference to the historical region of France. Home to vast lavender fields, and a population of wolves.

Her [[voice actor]] is [[Kageyama Akari]].

title: brave_commander_test_type
body:
[b]GNX-903VW Brave Commander Test Type[/b]
A more powerful variant of the Brave platform, the new generation of GN Drive Tau powered mobile suit. Unlike the standard type, it had two drives installed near its hips on side binders (although they are not configured to act as a Twin Drive System) and options for a third one in the typical position in the back, as well as longer commander antennas and further customization fitting of its left handed test pilot, [[Graham Aker]].

title: rozen_zulu
body:
[b]YAMS-132 Rozen Zulu[/b]
A highly modified, upgraded version of the [[Geara Zulu]] using spare parts from the [[Sinanju]] and design concepts from an old prototype MS, the [[Hamma Hamma]]. Equipped with wired claws controlled by a quasi-psycommu system, it allowed for even non-Newtype pilots, such as its owner [[Angelo Sauper]], to effectively battle Newtypes in conjunction with the Psyco Jammer anti-psycommu device.

* "Bulbapedia: Zisu":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Zisu]

Also known as the [i]Tiger Feint Kick[/i], it is a [[wrestling]] move popularized by [[WWE]] wrestler [[Rey Mysterio Jr]] (who named it after the area code of San Diego, California, his hometown).

It is done by a wrestler running and then jumping through the second and top rope while holding on to the ropes, using the momentum to perform a swinging kick to the head of an opponent who is hung on the second rope.

title: sekiguchi_hiroshi_no_tokyo_friend_park_ii
body:
"Tokyo Friend Park 2 (Japanese: 東京フレンドパークII; often abbreviated as "TFP2") is a Japanese game show that premiered in April 1994 on the Tokyo Broadcasting System ([[TBS]]). TFP2 airs on Monday nights roughly from 6:55 - 7:54 JST in Japan." [1]

h4. Darts

"At the end of each show, participants can choose between taking the coins (worth ¥100,000 each) or trading their coins in for darts; most contestants trade their coins for a dart each. Participants will then throw their darts at a large spinning dart-board. ... Prizes range from a high variety of electronics to a [new car].  If the contestant's dart lands in the gray center circle, or in one of the gray sections around the outside, the contestant will win a tawashi (a sponge, the show's joke prize). If the thrown dart misses the board and lands somewhere else (like the background or the floor), the participant's name will be written on the place it landed." [1]

When a contestant is readying to throw the dart, the crowd chants "Pajero". The "Mitsubishi Pajero":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitsubishi_Pajero] (known as the Montero or Shogun in some parts of the world) is an SUV that has traditionally been the top prize on the show. 

For an example of the darts segment, see "here":[https://vimeo.com/143764255] at 46m20s.

title: the_animage
body:
The★Animage is an original [[mecha]] [[model kit]] series that was released by ARII in 1981. (“The” is officially pronounced ZA/ðə.)
It is based on a fictional anime titled "Chou Ginga Densetsu Bison." ARII hoped to produce a real animated TV series with "Yoyogi Animation":[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BB%A3%E3%80%85%E6%9C%A8%E3%82%A2%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A1%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B7%E3%83%A7%E3%83%B3%E5%AD%A6%E9%99%A2], but the plan for this series was abandoned.
The succeeding series/second season toyline was simply called "The★Animage PART-II."

The comic booklets that came with the kits had serious picture quality issues. [[Kay Mowll]], the main heroine, was ridiculed for "having a different face every time she appeared in the story."

title: akai_koudan_zillion
body:
[b]Akai Koudan Zillion[/b] (赤い光弾ジリオン, lit. [i][b]Red Photon Zillion[/b][/i] in Japan), known elsewhere simply as [b][i]Zillion[/i][/b], is a [[1987]] [[science fiction]] anime series that originally ran from April 12, 1987 to December 13, 1987 on [[nippon_tv|Nippon Television]] and was produced by [[Tatsunoko Pro]]ductions, with promotional material published by [[Movic]]. 

After the production of the anime, Tatsunoko Production and Ishikawa Mitsuhisa, the producer of Zillion, established IG Tatsunoko (which later became [[Production I.G]]) to obstruct the dispersing of the excellent staffs of Tatsunoko branch which had done actual production. Therefore, Zillion is considered to be Production I.G's first work.

The anime was adapted into a [[Sega Master System]] [[video game]] called [i][b]Zillion[/b][/i]. This is an original space adventure platform video game developed by [[SEGA]] and designed for the Master System as a companion tie-in for Tatsunoko Production's Zillion anime series in 1987.

The Zillion series prominently features Sega's egg-shaped mascot, [[Opa-Opa]], who stars in the [[Fantasy Zone]] games, which are also available for the Master System. The main [[energy gun]] weapon of the anime is based on the design for the [[SEGA Light Phaser]] attachment for the [[game console]].

A sequel to the game, [i][b]Zillion II[/b][/i] was released in 1988.

[i][b]A Christmas Carol. In Prose. Being a Ghost Story of Christmas[/b][/i], commonly known as[b][i] A Christmas Carol[/i][/b], is a novella by Charles Dickens, first published in London by Chapman & Hall in 1843 and illustrated by John Leech. It has since become a fixture of the Christmas season in Western cultures, with multiple variations on the original story as well as parodied versions seen in other media.

title: keith_haring
body:
Keith Allen Haring (May 4, 1958 – February 16, 1990) was an American artist whose pop art emerged from the New York City graffiti subculture of the 1980s. His animated imagery has "become a widely recognized visual language". Much of his work includes sexual allusions that turned into social activism by using the images to advocate for safe sex and AIDS awareness. In addition to solo gallery exhibitions, he participated in renowned national and international group shows such as documenta in Kassel, the Whitney Biennial in New York, the São Paulo Biennial, and the Venice Biennale. The Whitney Museum held a retrospective of his art in 1997.

Notable work:
Keith Haring Mural (1984)
Crack is Wack (1986)
Tower (1987)
Todos Juntos Podemos Parar el SIDA (1989)
Tuttomondo (1989)

title: astaroth_(housamo)
body:
[[Tokyo Afterschool Summoners]] character.

His Sacred Artifact is a golden Snake that can perceive both past and future. Those afflicted by this serpent's venom will have their most deeply hidden memories exposed. Though only in speculation, there are some who consider these memories to be crimes one has committed in a past life or else future crimes yet to be committed. The memories that can be exposed include those regarding events beyond the 23 worlds connected to Tokyo. This is because powerful bonds between those who desire one another can cross even the wall that divides the worlds. It is said that if Astaroth himself is bitten, a woman with long, flowing hair that shines like the stars above will appear. In this Tokyo, one's Shadow and their original self are considered to be two separate entities, but in Astaroth's case, this is not entirely true. For to Astaroth, one's past life and future self are, in many ways, connected.

title: limiter_(tsukumo_sana)
body:
An accessory for the VTuber [[Tsukumo Sana]], who almost always wears it on her head like an [[ahoge]]. It's a thin, light-purple piece of material that sticks out from the top of the head and then spirals outward, similar to a mosquito coil. If a post clearly shows Sana not wearing her limiter, it's probably a case of the [[no headgear]] tag.

Lore-wise, it's meant to shrink her down to a size where she can safely interact with humans, since her true form is almost 1.7 billion metres tall and would make it impossible for her to be anywhere near Earth (which is only about 12.7 million metres wide) without immediately destroying it through sheer gravitational force.
